HEADWORD: Assiento
<hw>As`si*en"to</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>asiento</ets> seat, contract or agreement, fr. <ets>asentar</ets>
to place on a chair, to adjust, to make an agreement; <ets>a</ets> (L.
<ets>ad</ets>) + <ets>sentar</ets>, a participial verb; as if there were
a L. <ets>sedentare</ets> to cause to sit, fr. <ets>sedens</ets>,
<ets>sedentis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>sed⟦emac⟧re</ets> to sit.]</ety>
<def>A contract or convention between Spain and other powers for
furnishing negro slaves for the Spanish dominions in America, esp. the
contract made with Great Britain in 1713.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

